snippet.textDisplay:
WARNING: SPOILERS AHEAD
In my opinion, I don't think that Elsa should've been the 5th spirit.


If you really think about it, ice is basically water, just frozen. So if Elsa was the 5th spirit, that would basically mean that water is part of 2 spirits. Honestly, Anna should've been the 5th spirit; the spirit of love.
In the first Frozen film, both sisters accidentally let their powers loose. Elsa reveals her ice powers in front of the whole kingdom on the day that the castle gates opened and Anna accidentally let her powers loose by falling in love with the wrong man a.k.a Hans. After regaining control her powers, Elsa managed to break free from those chains and Anna regained control her powers when she was unfrozen by Elsa.


In the second movie, Anna is the only one in the franchise I would say that finds true love with Kristof, who is now her husband. Anna is the connection of Arrendale and the Enchanted Forest, not Elsa. It was Anna's idea to break down the dam, Anna who loved Elsa so much that she left Kristof behind and Anna who had a harder time to cope with Olaf fading away


Anna and Elsa together could create many amazing things. Take Olaf for instance. We all know that in the first film, he said that Elsa created him, but what I'm thinking is yeah, maybe Elsa did create him, but I don't ever remember her being able to bring things to life. I think that Elsa did literally create him, but Anna gave him enough love to become living.


And honestly, the whole movie revolved around Elsa, like, everything was about her. I think that Anna should've had some of that attention by being the fifth spirit. Elsa was the one who believed that she was the fifth spirit, the one who sent her sister and Olaf away, thinking that she was protecting them and Elsa was the one who woke the spirits to unleash their anger of being woken up on Arrendale. (I know the last one she did unintentionally, but honestly, what kind of a Queen goes out onto their balcony, shooting ice from their hands, out of the freaking palace, singing loud as hell and waking up the whole village?)


So that's my opinion.
Anna should've been the 5th spirit
because all this 'I'm the 5th spirit' thing is starting to increase Elsa's abnormally large ego.
:)

snippet.textDisplay: I just love how the meaning of 'Show Yourself' could be interpreted like this. In the beginning Elsa is telling what/whoever is 'hiding' to show themselves. But after she finds herself to be the one she's been searching for all her life, she sings 'Show Yourself' like she is telling herself to reveal who she is to everyone. Such a beautiful and meaningful song.
